import React from 'react'
import {ChakraProvider, Container, Box, Stack, Image, Heading, Text} from '@chakra-ui/react';

const Section7 = () => {
    return (
        <ChakraProvider>
            <Container maxW="1364px" h="1000px" bg="tomato">
                <Stack direction="row" spacing="100px" justify='center'>
                    <Box pt="150px">
                        <Box w="589px" bg="yellow.200">
                            <Image src="/Section/section6.png" />
                        </Box>
                    </Box>
                    <Box pt="300px">
                        <Stack direction="column" spacing="30px">
                            <Box w="390px" bg="yellow.200">
                                <Heading>Quick and easy account creation</Heading>
                            </Box>
                            <Box w="493px" h="189px" bg="gray.50">
                                <Text>Now, you might be thinking that it’s just like any other account creation… Long, tiresome and full of endless blanks to fill in. Well, it’s not.</Text>
                            </Box>
                        </Stack>
                    </Box>
                </Stack>
            </Container>
        </ChakraProvider>
    )
}

export default Section7
